      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Show two methods for the synthesis of dopamine, a neurotransmitter involved in regulation of the central nervous system. Use any alkyl halide needed.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdjBZIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--21c6d0b247bd609caff5128c4df9f9647e5e910d/OChem_24_06_007.jpg\" alt=\"The ball-and-stick model of dopamine. It comprises benzene ring with hydroxyl groups on C 1 and C 2, and C 4 has two methylene groups linked to an amine group.\">\n",
